description:
Cross-file interaction issue: crash_info_store() called from lora_l2.c:490 but lora state machine proceeds independently.

lora_l2.c:488-492:
  LOG_ERR('lora_l2: recv overflow (%d > %d)', ret, sizeof(rx_buf));
  crash_info_store(CRASH_DRIVER_OVERFLOW, __LINE__, ret);
  atomic_set(&current_state, LORA_ABORTED);
  break;

crash_info_store() at crash_info.c:18-47 writes to retained RAM but has no return value and cannot signal failure.

This is INTENTIONAL - crash_info is best-effort telemetry. But the cross-file contract is undocumented: lora_l2.c expects crash_info_store to succeed silently, and crash_info.c makes no guarantees.

If crash_info retained RAM is corrupted (magic never valid), crash_info_store continues without error. This is acceptable design but should be documented.

FIX: Add comment in lora_l2.c:490 noting crash_info_store is best-effort and does not affect recovery path.
